SIMPLE: prepare
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prepare
<hw>Pre*pare"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Prepared</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Preparing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧parer</ets>, L. <ets>praeparare</ets>; <ets>prae</ets>
before + <ets>parare</ets> to make ready. See <er>Pare</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To fit, adapt, or qualify for a particular purpose
or condition; to make ready; to put into a state for use or application;
<as>as, to <ex>prepare</ex> ground for seed; to <ex>prepare</ex> a
lesson.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our souls, not yet <qex>prepared</qex> for upper light.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To procure as suitable or necessary; to get ready;
to provide; <as>as, to <ex>prepare</ex> ammunition and provisions for
troops; to <ex>prepare</ex> ships for defence; to <ex>prepare</ex> an
entertainment.</as></def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That they may <qex>prepare</qex> a city for habitation.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. cvii. 36</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To fit; adjust; adapt; qualify; equip; provide;
form; make; make; ready.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1131 --></p>

<p><ent>Prepare</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prepare
<hw>Pre*pare"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
make all things ready; to put things in order; <as>as, to
<ex>prepare</ex> for a hostile invasion</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Bid them
<xex>prepare</xex> for dinner.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make one's self ready; to get ready; to take the
necessary previous measures; <as>as, to <ex>prepare</ex> for
death</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prepare</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prepare
<hw>Pre*pare"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Preparation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prepared</ent>⟦br⟧
